<item>
            <title>[TIKA-622] Switch from POIFSFileSystem to NPOIFSFileSystem, for speed and memory improvements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-622</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With POI 3.8 beta 1, there&apos;s an alternate OLE2 implementation NPOIFSFileSystem. From an API level, it&apos;s very similar to the existing POIFSFileSystem class, but internally it&apos;s lower memory and generally faster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While NPOIFSFileSystem is currently read only (the write support has a couple of gaps), for Tika&apos;s needs that isn&apos;t an issue&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should therefore switch our uses of POIFSFileSystem to NPOIFSFileSystem to reduce memory and enhance speed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
